projects.description:
During implementation of this payroll solution for this region I worked with the local teams (HR and Payroll) for the different countries (United Arab Emirates, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Oman, Qatar, Bahrain, Pakistan and Lebanon), Thales Global HRIS and payroll providers to successfully achieve the objectives and go-live.

During this implementation my responsibilities included:
- ensuring that business requirements are correctly and timely identified, are met and the solution is compliant with law and legislation. 
- steer, assist and help local team complete implementation activities such as design, integration mapping, SIT, UAT, parallel runs and data migration;
- providing status reports to the Group project team;
- managing the project deliverables in line with the project plan and current scope.

Working from the Netherlands, France and from the fourteen European countries of which I am the HRIS implementation lead, my responsibilities include country and stakeholder engagement, data gathering and acting as main point of contact between Group and country process owners. I am a member of the project core test team for HCM and Absence Management to provide feedback on business processes and the global design.

By working closely with HR Directors, Workday consultants and stakeholders I ensure that business requirements are met and the product is compliant with law and legislation. Other important responsibilities include:
- the monitoring project progress for each country;
- providing status reports to the Group project team;
- managing the project deliverables in line with the project plan and current scope;
- liaise with the change management team to ensure the successful implementation of Workday.
